{"lemma":"وَرَدَ","slug":"وَرَدَ","root":"#.ر.د","root_slug":"_-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ر-د","pos":"V","pos_camel":"verb","paradigm":[{"role":"past_2ms","form":"وَرَدْتَ","in_corpus":true,"count":23,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2fs","form":"وَرَدْتِ","in_corpus":true,"count":23,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2md","form":"وَرَدْتُما","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_2mp","form":"وَرَدْتُم","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_2fp","form":"وَرَدْتُنَّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3ms","form":"وَرَدَ","in_corpus":true,"count":81,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3fs","form":"وَرَدَت","in_corpus":true,"count":23,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3md","form":"وَرَدا","in_corpus":true,"count":9,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3fd","form":"وَرَدَتا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3mp","form":"وَرَدُوا","in_corpus":true,"count":3,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3fp","form":"وَرَدْنَ","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَرِد","in_corpus":true,"count":48,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَرِدِينَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَرِدِي","in_corpus":true,"count":4,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَرِدا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَرِدانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَرِدُوا","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَرِدُونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2fp","form":"تَرِدْنَ","in_corpus":true,"count":3,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَرِد","in_corpus":true,"count":145,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَرِد","in_corpus":true,"count":48,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَرِدا","in_corpus":true,"count":3,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَرِدانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَرِدا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَرِدانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَرِدُوا","in_corpus":true,"count":9,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَرِدُونَ","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَرِدْنَ","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَرِد","in_corpus":true,"count":3,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَرِد","in_corpus":true,"count":5,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"وَرَدْنا","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"وَرَدْتُ","in_corpus":true,"count":3,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"}],"frequency_in_corpus":438,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"وَرَدَ","root":"ورد","pos":"V","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41854","n41855"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to come, to arrive","examples":[{"text":"وَرَدَتْنِي عُرُوضٌ مِنْ كُلِّ أَنْحَاءِ ٱلْعَالَمِ.","english":"Offers from all over the world came to me."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to appear, to show up"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be said, to be mentioned","examples":[{"text":"أُرِيدُ أَنْ أَتَعَرَّفَ إِلَى أَبْرَزِ مَا وَرَدَ فِي الصِّحَافَةِ الدَّوْلِيَّةِ.","english":"I want to find out the most important things reported by the international press."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to import"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"watering hole"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"(esp. in plural) specified time of day or night devoted to private prayer"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"roses","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"الْوَرْدُ، الَّذِي قُبِلَ بِنَدَى الصَّبَاحِ، هَمَسَ أَسْرَارَ الْحُبِّ وَالْجَمَالِ لِلْعَالَمِ، وَزُهُورُهُ الرَّقِيقَةُ شَاهِدَةٌ عَلَى هَشَاشَةِ الْحَيَاةِ.","english":"The rose, kissed by the morning dew, whispered secrets of love and beauty to the world, its delicate petals a testament to the fragility of life."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blossoms","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to blossom, to be in bloom"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dye or paint red, to rouge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of وَرِيد (warīd)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *warad-. Cognate with Hebrew יָרַד (yārád, “to go down”), Aramaic ירד (yreḏ, “stream”), Ge'ez ወረደ (wärädä, “fall down, go down, drain off, pour down”), and Akkadian 𒉿𒊏𒁺𒌝 (warādum, “to go down to lower ground, to come ashore, to go downhill or downstream”) and Ugaritic 𐎊𐎗𐎄 (yrd).\n\nAs Aramaic וַרְדָּא (wardā), ܘܪܕܐ (wardā), Hebrew וֶרֶד (wéreḏ), and Old Armenian վարդ (vard) and Ancient Greek ϝρόδον (wródon), borrowed from a reflex of Proto-Iranian *wardah. Doublet of جُلّ (jull).\n\nDenominal verb of وَرْد (ward, “roses, blossoms”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41854","headword_ar":"وَرْدٌ","root":"wrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[coll. gen. n.] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flower,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blossom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any tree (AHn, L, K) or plant: (AHn, L:) but its predominant application is to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hawojam","text_ar":"حَوْجَم"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well-known red flower"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which one smells:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, TA:) its colour varies in winter and summer: (L:) and it is of different kinds in the cultivated soil and in the desert and in the mountains: (AHn, L:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L.) Said to be an arabicized word. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warodN","text_ar":"وَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A horse ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a bright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yellowish, bay colour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a colour between that called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kumayot","text_ar":"كُمَيْت"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oqar","text_ar":"اَشْقَر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L, K:) a horse, (M, L, Msb,) or other thing. (M, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a red colour inclining to yellow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, Msb,) beautiful in everything: (M, L:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L, Msb:) applied in the above sense to the sky, in the Kur, lv. 37: (L:) or it there means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roseates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a rosecolour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, L:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wurodN","text_ar":"وُرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juwnN","text_ar":"جُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawonN","text_ar":"جَوْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wiraAdN","text_ar":"وِرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aworaAdN","text_ar":"اَوْرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) but this last is unknown, and app. a mistake. (M, F, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warodN","text_ar":"وَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A lion"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the colour termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warod","text_ar":"وَرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutawar~idN","text_ar":"مُتَوَرِّدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iy~apN warodapN","text_ar":"عَشِيَّةٌ وَرْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An evening when the horizon is red"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at sunset;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is a sign of drought: and in like manner the morning at sunrise. (L.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN warodapN","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ وَرْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A night of which the beginning and end are red;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is the case in a time of drought. (A.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warodN","text_ar":"وَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"daring;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) an epithet applied to a man; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAridN","text_ar":"وَارِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warodN","text_ar":"وَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Saffron."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwarodu AljabaliY~u","text_ar":"الوَرْدُ الجَبَلِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaAlN","text_ar":"عَبَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw Alwarodi","text_ar":"اَبُو الوَرْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The penis:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) so called because of its redness. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["AHn","L","K","TA","S","M","Msb","Zj","A"]},{"entry_id":"n41855","headword_ar":"وِرْدٌ","root":"wrd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A coming to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arriving at, water &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether one enters it or does not enter it; (S, * L, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadarN","text_ar":"صَدَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L, Msb.) See also 1. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wirodN","text_ar":"وِرْدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water to which one comes to drink."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wirodN","text_ar":"وِرْدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The time of the day of coming to water, between the two periods of abstaining from water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turn, of coming to water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hzb","text_ar":"حزب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wirodN","text_ar":"وِرْدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The arrival of the day of coming to water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waradati AlA_ibilu AlmaA='a wirodFA","text_ar":"وَرَدَتِ الاـِبِلُ المَا=ءَ وِرْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aworaAdF","text_ar":"اَوْرَادً"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ayoru","text_ar":"الطَّيْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the birds, came to the water in a herd,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a flock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in herds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in flocks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wir~dN","text_ar":"وِرّدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company of men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a number of camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of birds, &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arriving at, water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAridapN","text_ar":"وَارِدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, Msb, K:) the former originally an inf. n.: (Msb:) its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aworaAdN","text_ar":"اَوْرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAridN","text_ar":"وَارِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wirodN","text_ar":"وِرْدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A herd of camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A flock of birds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) ―         -b9-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An army,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K,) so called as being likened to a herd of camels, or to a flock of birds. (L.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"share, of water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thirst."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasuwqu Almujorimiyna","text_ar":"نَسُوقُ المُجْرِمِينَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY jahay~ama wirodFA","text_ar":"اـِلَى جَهَيَّمَ وِرْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[Kur, xix, 89,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We will drive the sinners to hell like beasts that come to water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thirsty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Beyd:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walking and thirsty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, L.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wirodN","text_ar":"وِرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"day of a fever, when it attacks the patient periodically:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, L, Msb, * K *:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the names of fever:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) but the former explanation is the more correct. (TA.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wirodN","text_ar":"وِرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion of the night when a man has to pray."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b15-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wirodN","text_ar":"وِرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A section,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"division,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Kur-án:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a set portion of recitation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain portion of the Kur-án,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a seventh, or half a seventh, or the like, (Mgh, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which a person recites at a particular time:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a set portion of the Kur-án,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of prayer; &c., of which a man imposes upon himself the recital on a particular occasion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at a particular time; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HizobN","text_ar":"حِزْبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"q. v.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, L:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aworaAdN","text_ar":"اَوْرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, Msb.) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraA^otu wirodiY","text_ar":"قَرَاْتُ وِرْدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I recited my set portion of the Kur-án, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, L:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lifulaAnK kul~a layolapK wirodN","text_ar":"لِفُلَانٍ كُلَّ لَيْلَةٍ وِرْدٌ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2936},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlquroA=ni yaqoraA^uhu","text_ar":"مِنَ القُرْا=نِ يَقْرَاُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has every night a set portion of the Kur-án which he recites."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["L","S","Msb","K","Beyd","Mgh"]}]}}